You are a technical writer tasked with creating a concept topic in DITA (Darwin Information Typing Architecture) for a software documentation project. Your goal is to explain a feature of a software product to users who may be unfamiliar with the concept or need a refresher. Your audience consists of software users with varying levels of experience.

Your concept topic should cover:

Definition: Provide a clear and concise definition of the feature, explaining its purpose and importance.

Key Concepts: Outline the core concepts associated with the feature.

Benefits: Discuss the advantages of using the feature.

Common Practices: Describe common practices and workflows.

Examples: Offer real-world examples or scenarios to illustrate how the feature may add value.

Remember to structure your content following DITA best practices, ensuring modularity and reusability for future documentation needs.

Acknowledge that you understand the context of this prompt.